Feature list for todolist

Core

Weekly System

7 fixed daily task lists (Monday–Sunday)
Tasks automatically belong to a specific weekday
System always regenerates the correct day view
No manual resetting required

Daily Update Logic

Detect current date
Compare with last saved active day
Trigger rollover when day changes
Move unfinished tasks to Extra list

Custom Day Reset Time

User can choose what time the “day” changes
Example: 04:00 instead of 00:00
System checks current time
If current time passes chosen reset time:
→ Update active day
→ Run rollover logic
Reset time stored in settings

Task Management

Add task
Remove task
Edit task
Mark task complete
Mark task incomplete

Extra (Overflow) List

Automatically receives unfinished daily tasks
Separate from weekly structure
Can manually add/remove tasks
Can mark as completed

Separate Custom Lists

User-created lists independent of daily system
Add list
Delete list
Manage tasks inside them

Habit System

Mark a task as a habit
Track habit completion history
Calculate streaks
Calculate weekly consistency
Show habit-specific stats

Reward System

Define rewards
Reward triggers based on:
Completing full day
Maintaining habit for X days
Completing specific extra list
Reward eligibility rules
Reward unlocking logic

Consistency Tracking

Daily completion percentage
Weekly completion percentage
Habit streak length
Overall performance stats

Time Handling

Store reset time setting
Compare current time to reset time
Trigger day transition logic

DATA LAYER (Storage)

This layer only handles saving and loading.

It does NOT decide rules.

Features:

Data Storage

Store tasks
Store daily structure
Store extra list
Store custom lists
Store habits
Store rewards
Store settings (including reset time)

Load Data

Load everything at app start

Save Data

After any change

Export Data

Create backup file
Save to user-chosen location

Import Data

Restore from backup file

Recommended storage option:

SQLite database (clean and structured)
OR
Structured JSON file (simpler but less powerful)

INTERFACE LAYER (UI)

This layer is just how the user interacts.

You can build multiple versions later.

CLI Interface

Show today’s tasks
Add task
Complete task
View habits
View rewards
Change reset time
Export data

GUI Interface (Later)

Buttons for tasks
Visual daily view
Habit screen
Reward screen
Settings screen
Sound when completing tasks
Visual animations

Web Interface (Future)

Browser-based version
Connects to same core logic
Same data structure